!git status
!git diff --staged

Based on the changes above, create a commit following conventional commits:

Format: `type(scope): description`

Types: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, test, chore

1. Review staged changes
2. Write concise, descriptive commit message
3. Create the commit
4. Show the commit log